UI & CONSOLE DESIGN TEST CASES

1. TITLE & HEADER FORMAT
- Title text appears in correct color (CYAN)
- Proper spacing before and after title
- No text overlap


2. HORIZONTAL LINE CONSISTENCY
- Lines use consistent characters ('-' or custom)
- Correct length (40, 30, 80, etc.)
- Lines align with table width


3. MENU ALIGNMENT
- Menu options aligned properly (1–10)
- No shifting due to double-digit numbers
- Equal spacing between options


4. TEXT COLOR CONSISTENCY
- Headers → YELLOW
- Prices → MAGENTA
- Titles → CYAN
- Total → GREEN
- Colors reset properly after each line


5. TABLE STRUCTURE (BOOKS, CART, BILL)
- Columns aligned using fixed width
- Vertical separators (|) properly placed
- Header and data rows match in width


6. COLUMN WIDTH HANDLING
- Book Name column fits within defined width (30 chars)
- Overflow text breaks layout (known limitation)
- Numeric fields remain right-aligned


7. SPACING & PADDING
- Proper spacing between columns
- Uniform padding using %-format specifiers
- No cramped or uneven text


8. SECTION SEPARATION
- Clear gaps between:
  - Menus
  - Tables
  - Bill section
- Improves readability


9. CONSISTENT TABLE WIDTH
- Borders match content width exactly
- No mismatch between header and rows


10. NUMBER FORMATTING DISPLAY
- Prices show exactly 2 decimal places
- Alignment remains intact with larger numbers


11. TERMINAL COMPATIBILITY
- ANSI colors display correctly in supported terminals
- Graceful fallback (readable text) if colors unsupported


12. VISUAL FLOW
- UI follows clear order:
  Title → Menu → Tables → Summary
- Easy to read without confusion


13. CLEAN OUTPUT TERMINATION
- Ends with "Program ended."
- No broken formatting at end
